      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver must have documented verification test suite and version-controlled release process consistent with MRL 2 requirements.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 used with documented QA procedures including regression test suite, formal release notes, and version control. Software validation records confirm compliance with FDA software quality guidance at the level required for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations through benchmark problems with known analytical solutions at MRL 2 level.",
      "rationale": "Code verification performed using lid-driven cavity benchmark and Taylor-Green vortex test cases. Observed order of accuracy consistent with theoretical second-order convergence for the finite-volume discretisation employed. Results documented in solver verification report."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) for hemolysis index QoI must be less than 5% at the operating conditions of interest.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study conducted at 4.5 L/min, 3500 RPM nominal operating point. GCI for normalised hemolysis index computed as 2.8%, satisfying the 5% acceptance criterion. Asymptotic range confirmed with GCI ratio of 1.02."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental validation test conditions must overlap with at least 4 of the 5 target flow-speed combinations specified in the COU.",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis data collected at 3 L/min, 4 L/min, 4.5 L/min, and 6 L/min flow rates at rotational speeds from 2500 to 4500 RPM, covering 4 of 5 COU operating points. Temperature, hematocrit (35%), and blood analog fluid properties controlled and documented per ASTM F1841."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) must agree with experimental measurements within 20% across all validated operating points.",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted NIH values compared against experimental measurements at 4 operating points. Maximum relative error of 14.3% observed at 6 L/min, 4500 RPM; mean absolute relative error of 9.7% across all points. All predictions within the 20% acceptance band. Bland-Altman analysis confirms absence of systematic bias."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (NIH, RH index) must be directly mappable to the clinical hemolysis endpoint relevant to the COU decision.",
      "rationale": "Normalised index of hemolysis and relative hemolysis index (RH) are established surrogates for clinical hemolysis risk in rotary blood pumps, referenced in FDA guidance on pump hemolysis testing. Direct correspondence between computational QoI and the RH < 1 acceptance criterion in the COU is demonstrated."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, flow regime, and fluid properties must be sufficiently similar to the COU device and operating envelope to support credibility at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which shares impeller topology and Reynolds number regime with the CPB device under assessment. Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water) used in experiments with matched viscosity. Geometric similarity ratio documented as 1:1 for impeller diameter. Validation activities assessed as adequately relevant to COU at MRL 2."
    },
    {
